<head>
  <%- include('./partials/head') %> <%- include('./partials/pageTopFeatures') %>

  <title><%= server.appName %> - Privacy Policy <%if (server.logLevel !== "info") {%> (<%= server.logLevel %>) <%}%></title>
    </head>

    <body class="bg-dark text-light">
      <%- include('./partials/adTopBar') %>
    <%- include('./partials/navbar', {user: user}) %>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col p-md-2 m-md-3">
          <h1 class="h3 mt-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-quaternary"><small>Last updated: July 13, 2026</small></p>

          <p class="mt-3">
            This instance of <%= server.appName %> at <strong>nets.n1cck.radio</strong> is a
            personal, non-commercial service operated by Nick Booth (N1CCK) for the amateur-radio
            community. This policy describes what data the service collects and how it is used.
            Questions or requests: <a href="mailto:nick@n1cck.us">nick@n1cck.us</a>.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">What we collect</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Account information</strong> — your email address, callsign, display name,
              and (optionally) a location you provide.</li>
            <li><strong>Net activity</strong> — check-ins, signal reports, roles, timestamps, and
              other records generated when you participate in a net, plus chat messages sent during
              a net.</li>
            <li><strong>Technical data</strong> — a signed session cookie (see the
              <a href="/views/cookiepolicy">Cookie Policy</a>) and routine server logs (IP address,
              request paths, timestamps) kept for security and troubleshooting.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">How it is used</h2>
          <p>
            Solely to operate the service: signing you in, running nets, showing presence and
            check-in lists to other participants, and sending transactional email (sign-in links
            and net notifications). No advertising, no marketing email, and no sale or sharing of
            personal data for commercial purposes — ever.
          </p>
          <p>
            Note that net participation is inherently visible to other users: your callsign,
            display name, and check-in activity appear to participants and followers of a net,
            consistent with the public nature of amateur-radio operation.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            This instance uses a <strong>self-hosted</strong> Plausible Analytics server operated
            by the same operator. It is cookieless, collects only aggregate usage statistics (page
            views, referrers, browser family), does not track you across sites, and no analytics
            data leaves the operator's infrastructure.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Service providers</h2>
          <p>Limited data is shared with these processors, only as needed for the feature involved:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Google</strong> — only if you choose "Sign in with Google" (your Google
              account email is used to authenticate you).</li>
            <li><strong>GetStream (Stream.io)</strong> — real-time chat; chat messages and your
              display identity are processed by Stream to deliver chat.</li>
            <li><strong>QRZ.com</strong> — callsigns are looked up to enrich station profiles with
              publicly available license data.</li>
            <li><strong>Microsoft Azure Maps</strong> — coordinates you choose to share are
              reverse-geocoded to a place name.</li>
            <li><strong>Email (SMTP) relay</strong> — your email address is processed by the
              operator's mail relay to deliver sign-in links and notifications.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>The database is self-hosted on the operator's own server; no managed database provider
            receives your data.</p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Retention and deletion</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>You can delete your account at any time from the in-app
              <strong>Data Privacy</strong> page; deletion removes your account data from the
              service.</li>
            <li>Inactive accounts are flagged and automatically deleted after roughly 180 days of
              inactivity.</li>
            <li>Net logs (check-in records) are retained as part of a net's history and may be
              emailed to the net owner when a net closes.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Security</h2>
          <p>
            The service is reachable only over HTTPS, sessions use signed HTTP-only cookies, and
            credentials/secrets are stored in a dedicated secrets manager, not in code.
            No internet service can guarantee absolute security; use a unique credential where
            applicable.
          </p>

          <h2 class="h5 mt-4">Changes</h2>
          <p>
            Material changes to this policy will be reflected on this page with an updated date
            above. Continued use of the service after a change constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('./partials/pageBottomFeatures') %>
    </body>
    <%- include('./partials/footer') %>

</html>
